        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 4:00PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 400 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Hazen, or 7 miles northeast of Lahontan Reservoir,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fallon, Hazen, and Junction U.S 50 And NV 117 (sheckler Cutoff).
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
